I built this project for an E-commerce client who was struggling with high customer support volume. I implemented a RAG-based AI assistant that ingests all their product manuals, return policies, FAQs and warranty documents into ChromaDB as vector embeddings. When a customer asks a question, the system retrieves the top 3 most relevant chunks and passes them to GPT-2 to generate an accurate answer. This reduced their support response time from 30 minutes to 3 seconds.




- Developed an AI-powered document assistant using RAG 
  architecture that reduced customer support response 
  time from 30 minutes to 3 seconds

- Implemented document ingestion pipeline that 
  automatically loads and processes multiple PDF 
  documents including product manuals, FAQs, return 
  policies and warranty documents

- Built vector embedding pipeline using HuggingFace 
  sentence-transformers (all-MiniLM-L6-v2) and stored 
  embeddings in ChromaDB vector database for 
  efficient similarity search

- Integrated GPT-2 language model for generating 
  accurate context-aware answers based on retrieved 
  document chunks

- Developed interactive chat interface using Streamlit 
  with chat history, source references and 
  real-time responses

- Implemented caching mechanism using Streamlit's 
  cache_resource to optimize model loading 
  and improve performance



  AI-Powered E-commerce Product Assistant
Technologies: Python, LangChain, ChromaDB, HuggingFace, 
              Streamlit, GPT-2
Domain: Generative AI | RAG | NLP

- Developed AI chatbot for E-commerce client using RAG 
  architecture reducing support response time by 95%

- Built automated PDF ingestion pipeline processing 
  multiple documents including FAQs, return policies 
  and product manuals simultaneously

- Implemented vector similarity search using ChromaDB 
  and HuggingFace embeddings (all-MiniLM-L6-v2) for 
  accurate document retrieval

- Integrated GPT-2 LLM for generating context-aware 
  answers grounded in company documents preventing 
  hallucination

- Deployed interactive chat UI using Streamlit with 
  real-time responses and source citation features